LEFT function

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| LEFT(string, length, [pad])                                                 |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

Returns a string composed of the leftmost length characters of the string,
extended with the pad character as necessary.

Examples:

    LEFT('abc d',8)     == 'abc d   '
    LEFT('abc d',8,'.') == 'abc d...'
    LEFT('abc  def',7)  == 'abc  de'